%% Argo Workflows - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant DSP as DSP API Server
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant WFC as workflow-controller<br/>SA: argo
    participant Pod as Workflow Step Pod<br/>(argoexec sidecar)
    participant S3 as S3/MinIO Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP

    Note over DSP,DB: Flow 1: Workflow Execution (Primary - RHOAI/DSP)

    DSP->>K8s: Create Workflow CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8s-->>WFC: Watch notification (informer)<br/>TLS 1.2+
    WFC->>K8s: Create Pod (workflow step)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Note over Pod: argoexec runs as<br/>sidecar/init container
    K8s-->>Pod: Pod scheduled & started

    Pod->>S3: Download input artifacts<br/>Auth: Access Key/Secret Key
    S3-->>Pod: Artifact data
    Note over Pod: Execute workflow step<br/>container logic
    Pod->>S3: Upload output artifacts<br/>Auth: Access Key/Secret Key
    Pod->>K8s: Report task result<br/>(WorkflowTaskResult CR)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8s-->>WFC: TaskResult watch notification
    WFC->>K8s: Update Workflow status<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Note over DSP,DB: Flow 2: Workflow Archival (Optional)

    WFC->>DB: Archive workflow data<br/>Auth: Username/Password<br/>TLS (configurable)

    Note over DSP,DB: Flow 3: Cron Workflow Scheduling

    K8s-->>WFC: CronWorkflow watch notification
    WFC->>K8s: Create Workflow from CronWorkflow<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
